 source environment, rather than by unrelated foreground\nmagnetoionic material. In addition, a significant fraction (21%) of sources\nexhibit \"repolarization\", which further suggests that polarized SEDs are\naffected by different emitting regions within the source, rather than by a\nparticular depolarization law. This has implications for the physical\ninterpretation of future broadband polarimetric surveys.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 10 Mar 2014 20:00:50 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 1 Oct 2015 14:28:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-10-02"}
