 satellites,\nbut their radial distribution remains significantly shallower than observed. It\nseems that most satellites of low-mass primaries can continue to form stars\neven after orbiting within their joint halo for 5 Gyr or more.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 10 Mar 2014 21:00:21 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 16 May 2014 10:57:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-06-13"}
