 comet activity driven by the\nevaporation of water ice, we derive a minimum size for the dust aggregates of\n$\\sim 1$ mm, in agreement with meteoroid observations and dust-agglomeration\nmodels in the solar nebula. Finally we conclude that cometesimals must have\nformed by gravitational instability, because all alternative formation models\nlead to higher tensile strengths of the surface layers.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 11 Mar 2014 15:21:32 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 21 Nov 2014 10:13:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-19"}
